answerText: Max Beerbohm[10] In "Enoch Soames," Enoch calls this poet "second-rate" and claims that he possesses "a deadly evenness."  This poet wrote of a pedestal proclaiming "look on my works, ye mighty, and despair" in "Ozymandias."

question: Question: He discussed an "Oxford Love Story" in Zuleika Dobson. For 10 points each: [10] Name this British author who also wrote about a writer who makes a pact with a devil to time travel to the British Museum reading room in 1997 in "Enoch Soames."
